# Courtify agent practices

Full context lives in `AGENTS.md` (start with **Agent quick start**). Do not re-invent patterns already implemented there.

## UI/UX (F1-app style)

- **Layouts:** `Courtify/Shared/CourtifyLayout.swift` only — `CourtifyFullBleedScreen` (Home), `CourtifyHeroScrollScreen` (Schedule/Rankings), `CourtifyPlainScrollScreen` (Widgets).
- **Safe-area traps (fixed — do not reintroduce):**
  1. Never `.ignoresSafeArea(edges: .top)` on a view wrapping a `GeometryReader` (safeTop becomes 0).
  2. Never offset hero background up inside a `ScrollView` (clips → dark band under status bar). ScrollView gets `.ignoresSafeArea(edges: .top)`; pad hero *content* with safeTop.
  3. Never put paywall behind `OnboardingFlowView`’s top `safeAreaInset` chrome — solid band over the live marquee (blackout). Paywall owns full-bleed backdrop + close (`managesOwnCloseButton`).
- **Chrome:** OLED black (`ThemeManager.oledBlack`) canvas + `CourtifyAmbientGlow` (heroes) / `CourtifyListAmbientBloom` (list/grid screens: Schedule, Rankings, Settings, Onboarding). Frosted cards via `.courtifyGlassSurface` / `.glassCard` — **pure** `.ultraThinMaterial` + `ThemeManager.glassEdge` (white **15%**, 0.5pt). Never solid grey card fills; never `CourtifyAmbientGlow` clipped inside a card (kills glass). Native `TabView` + `CourtifyTabBarChrome`; active tint `ThemeManager.brandYellow`. `ProfileIconButton` + `.settingsSheet` on **all four tabs**.
- **Onboarding selection:** `.courtifySelectableCard` for tour grids, player posters, slam list rows — scale 1.03 / 1.02, 1.5pt yellow border, yellow glow, selection haptic. Progress bar: 3pt `brandYellow` + glow.
- **Onboarding CTAs:** `.courtifyPrimaryButtonLabel()` (Capsule yellow glow); `.courtifyDormantButtonLabel()` for pre-pick disabled state; `.courtifySecondaryButtonLabel()` for Skip glass pill; “Not now” = plain white @ 60% ghost (no pill).
- **Splash:** marquee `.drawingGroup` + `.blur(16)` + black 0.65 scrim; title 48pt black rounded; subtitle `.title3` @ 80% white.
- **Motion:** `CourtifyMotion` + `.courtifyButton(...)` only (soft `sensoryFeedback` on press-down). Root `.courtifyInteractiveChrome()` covers every `Button` **and** non-button surface taps (subtle window scale/dim + soft haptic — no per-screen wiring). Selection uses `.courtifySelectionFeedback`. No new haptics/animation curves.
- Use `WidgetTheme.contentInset` (16pt) for all small/medium copy — do not invent per-widget padding. Home widgets use `WidgetTheme.contentInsets` (adds stamp clearance at the bottom). Atmospheric `WidgetAtmosphere` / `WidgetTextureOverlay` (aurora default; carbon/mesh/spotlight/velvet optional) beat flat single-color fills; skip muddy tournament logos as backgrounds. Overlay chrome must stay inside the preview-sized ZStack (never `maxWidth: .infinity` overlays that stretch a lone small card). Keep hero cutouts and stats in separate columns on medium cards. Lock Screen gallery previews use `LockScreenGalleryFrame` + frosted plate (no white stroke). Unlocked card tap → `WidgetShareView` (`.courtifyButton(.card)` haptic) with Share → system share sheet; locked → paywall. Share asset includes **Made by Courtify on App Store** stamp (`MadeByCourtifyAppStoreStamp`). **Widget stamp:** `WidgetMadeByStamp` via `.courtifyWidgetCanvas()` — opticYellow, not grey; keep clear of bottom copy via `contentInsets`.
- **Made by Courtify stamp:** home-screen WidgetKit uses `.courtifyWidgetCanvas()` + `WidgetMadeByStamp`. In-app Widgets Collection / share previews set `.environment(\.showsWidgetMadeByStamp, false)` so gallery cards stay clean. Lock Screen: `stamp: .none` only.
- **Widget colors (Premium):** `WidgetColorStyle` + `WidgetColorPickerSheet` for all home-screen gallery cards (`favorite` / tournaments / standings / `live` / `order`). Includes **Tournament** theme (live slam/surface brand — default for `next-*` / `countdown` / `calendar`), named presets (Clay/Grass/…), **Custom** `ColorPicker`, plus **Texture** (Aurora default; hidden while Tournament theme is selected). Defaults (Jul 2026): **content-based colors, shared neon-grid texture** — favorite = OLED black `0x0B0B0D` (`favoriteOLEDDefault`), ATP = hardcourt navy preset, WTA = berry preset, live = near-black `0x121212`, order = AO sky; all use `WidgetTexturePreset.neonGrid` (Tron light-grid floor via `NeonGridOverlay` + glass specular hairline; carbon hatch was rejected as Android-looking, green gradient as cheap, a single unified black as too samey). **No horizon line** — a bright glowing horizon read as a green glitch/strikethrough across every widget; floor grid only. Favorite views add the `WidgetLEDAccent` tick. `WidgetTheme.neonLine(for:)`: colored accents glow neon in their own hue (sat/brightness floored), neutral near-blacks glow opticYellow. Non-default app themes still map the favorite accent; hardcourt/berry/AO-sky remain presets. Free users tapping the gallery color control open the paywall (never the sheet). Free users tapping locked Premium widget cards also open the paywall. Gradient slider persists on finger-up only (no per-tick timeline reload). Sheet defaults to `.large`; gradient + texture sit above the preset grid when not on Tournament theme.
- **App appearance (Premium):** Settings → App theme + Logo ball via `AppAppearanceStore` (defaults named **Courtify**). Free → Premium badge + paywall.
- **Custom player photos:** `PlayerTorsoPhotoView` / `TennisPlayerPhotoView` + monochrome `PlayerSilhouetteView` (`figure.tennis` for **both** tours — never the restroom-pair `figure.dress.line.vertical.figure`) — never letter placeholders, never a gradient/fill wash behind torso silhouettes.
- **Bundled hero cutouts:** `TennisPlayer.bundledHeroCutoutName` resolves `player-{id}-hero` (featured) then `player-{name-slug}-hero` (search catalog + live top-10, 41 assets added Jul 2026). All hero surfaces (Home, Settings, widgets, onboarding posters) check it first, so custom picks like Dimitrov/Ruud get real bodyshots. Never hand-build hero asset names; new cutouts are dev-time downloads (ATP via a real browser session — Cloudflare blocks curl **and** Worker fetches; WTA via curl + `api.wtatennis.com` search). Verify ATP codes against atptour.com profile URLs (wrong code → silent 300×300 placeholder; Ruud `rh16`, Rune `r0dg`, Berrettini `bk40`).
- **Home slam countdown card:** slam-branded `SlamCardTheme` gradients (USO navy+yellow, AO sky+white, RG clay+green, WIM green+lavender), one 1pt accent hairline, 10pt bottom margin above the tab bar; countdown digits and Get Premium pill `.fixedSize()` so they never wrap.
- **Settings favorite cards:** equal-width `FavoriteCard`s (`minWidth: 0`); artwork overlay-only; Change padded above corner radius. Slam art via `FavoriteSlamLogoBadge`. True quota miss → silhouette + short helper; inactive/not-found → silent silhouette. RapidAPI studio JPEGs render as circular headshots — never grey rectangular “cutouts.”
- **Paywall / splash backdrop:** `CourtifyMarqueeBackground` — live SwiftUI widget cards (not `marquee-widget-strip`, not player photos). Avoid positive marquee `startOffset` gutters (left blackout strip).
- **WidgetKit:** register every gallery card via `CourtifyWidgetCatalog` + nested `OtherBundle().body` when exceeding 10 kinds (do not pass a `WidgetBundle` type as a `Widget`). Lock Screen kinds live in `LockScreenWidgets.swift`.
- **Lock Screen chrome:** `AccessoryWidgetBackground` via `containerBackground` only — no white `strokeBorder`, no `contentMarginsDisabled`, no `courtifyWidgetCanvas` max-frame fill, `stamp: .none`. Short copy (`USO` / `NYC`). Locked CTA: upright `CourtifyWordmark` (“Subscribe to COURTIFY”). Gallery: Lockscreen filter, no purple preview plates, Free/Premium beside section titles. Test via axe (see `AGENTS.md` → Lock Screen widget testing); gallery QA with `-UITestWidgetOnly lock-*`.
- **Slam logos (pickers):** `AssetCatalogImage` — not `CachedBundledImage` (stale in-memory cache). All slam logos in rows/cards go through shared `SlamLogoBadge` (circular, brand-tinted, `scaledToFill`) — never raw `.fit` logos in mixed-shape lists.
- **`.fill` cutouts in fixed cards:** fixed `.frame(width:height:alignment: .top)` + `.clipped()` on the image — flexible max-infinity frames report the overflow height and inflate the card's ZStack (cropped heads + clipped rank labels on onboarding posters, Jul 2026).
- **Retired legends:** `TennisPlayer.retiredLegendCareerRecords` (slug-keyed, verified career W/L) → `isRetiredLegend` / `careerRecord`. Home hero shows "Legend" copy; widgets put career W/L in the big rank slot (verbatim, no LEGEND wordmark — too loud at widget scale). Enrichment + refresh heal skip legends (doomed lookups). Never render "—" in any widget — omit missing stats instead. Gallery section order: home favorite → Lock Screen chapter (led by free lock favorite) → tournaments → standings → live. Small favorite widget name needs `.fixedSize(horizontal: false, vertical: true)` to keep both lines.

## API cost (strict)

**Upstream plan:** RapidAPI Matchstat **Pro ($29/mo)** on Tennis API - ATP WTA ITF. Basic (50 req/day) is **not** viable for custom photos / season W/L. Do not migrate vendors without an explicit product decision.

| Data | Source | When it fetches |
|------|--------|-----------------|
| Favorite player hero (bundled) | `player-*-hero` assets | Never at runtime |
| Custom favorite rank/photo | `/api/player-lookup` (+ optional verified `apiId` hint → profile fallback for outside-top-100 ranks) + `/api/player-photo` | **On pick only**; Worker KV 30d (7d profile-sourced) + edge photo 30d (head+hero = one edge entry) |
| Custom favorite season W/L | `/api/player-season-record` → `PlayerSeasonRecordCache` | **On pick** (always, even if photo 404/429); **heal on pull-to-refresh** only when season **or rank** missing for the active `custom:` favorite. Worker KV 24h |
| Tournament schedule | `TournamentCalendar` | Never |
| Rankings / live / order of play / Home favorite rank | Worker via `WidgetDataStore` | Pull-to-refresh only (Home, Rankings, Widgets) |
| Onboarding top-10 player row | Worker | **Once ever** via `refreshOnceForOnboarding()` |

On appear: `loadCachedPayload()` only (always reload from app-group disk). No `refresh()` without user pull or the one-time onboarding exception.

**Onboarding picks:** Tour / favorite player / Grand Slam write to app-group keys as the user continues each step. Home is gated on `hasCompletedOnboarding` only — never skip onboarding solely because RevenueCat Pro or referral bypass flipped mid-flow (drops unsaved favorites).

**Quota:** Do not expand widget-data to top 100. Do not mass-fetch season W/L inside shared refresh (one-player heal when active custom favorite cache is nil is OK). Lookup = one rankings call per uncached name, no 429 retries. Photos go through Worker edge cache (**one** RapidAPI image per player; head+hero share edge key). On 429/503 **widget-data** refresh, show alert and keep cached rankings. Custom photo: true quota → short helper; HTTP 404/empty/inactive → **silent** silhouette (`.notFound`, never blame “daily API limit”). Never treat RapidAPI studio JPEGs as torso cutouts (circular headshot or silhouette). Worker skips RapidAPI when remaining &lt; reserve (5 Basic-sized / 100 Pro+). After Basic→Pro upgrade, delete stale KV `rapidapi-quota` if photos still 429.

**Do not:** UGC player photo upload; typographic initials fallback; WidgetKit network calls; per-match live polling; monthly rankings refresh (use 6 h on-demand + pull-to-refresh).

Worker: on-demand KV refresh (max every 6 h), **5** upstream calls (live + ATP/WTA rankings + ATP/WTA fixtures), ATP/WTA top 20 (`pageSize=20`). Deploy: `npx wrangler deploy`.

**Upstream path trap:** player-stats endpoints (surface-summary, profile) route **without** the `ms-api` prefix on the umbrella product — the Matchstat docs' `ms-api` paths 404. Only `uploads/Photo` keeps `ms-api`. `WidgetDataStore.lastUpdated` = device `lastSyncedAt` (every successful fetch), not raw `payload.updatedAt` (6 h server cadence) — don't revert.

## Simulator testing (no tap automation)

- Simulator: iPhone 17 Pro `744F6ACA-F0CC-4105-8794-D798EF7726CC`
- **Default dev loop:** `bash scripts/dev-sim-hot-reload.sh` (UI + backend). Avoid Xcode Canvas — large asset catalog causes "empty catalog import…" and high CPU. See `AGENTS.md` → **Local dev modes**.
- **After asset or cache changes:** `simctl uninstall … com.courtify.xyz` before reinstall.
- Build: `xcodebuild … -derivedDataPath .derivedData` → `simctl install` → `simctl launch`
- Launch args: `-UITestHome`, `-UITestTab schedule|rankings|widgets`, `-UITestSettings`, `-UITestWidgetFilter`, `-UITestWidgetOnly <id>`, `-UITestPaywall`, `-UITestOnboarding tour|players|slam|notifications` (onboarding QA — prefer over axe tap; axe hangs on splash)
- Lock Screen: gallery QA via `-UITestWidgetOnly lock-*` (`lock-badge`, `lock-badge-rect`, `lock-rank`, `lock-player`, `lock-season`, `lock-season-rect`, `lock-countdown`, `lock-next`, `lock-live`); real install via axe (not simctl) — see `AGENTS.md` → **Lock Screen widget testing**
- Wait ~7s after launch before screenshots.
- Seed rankings: write `widgetDataPayloadCache` hex to app-group plist.
- When verifying insets from screenshots, measure at 3× (iPhone 17 Pro); anti-aliased card edges can under-count padding by ~6px.

## Release

- Bump `CURRENT_PROJECT_VERSION` in `Courtify.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj` before TestFlight
- Upload: `bash scripts/upload-testflight.sh` (uses `scripts/xcode-env.sh` → Xcode 26.0.1)
- Commit/push when the user asks; deploy Worker after `index.js` changes
